This paper deals with web search data analysis and its application to estimate influenza-like illness (ILI) activity. Therefore, the most likely category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR), which deals with search engines and information retrieval systems. The paper also involves statistical modeling and analysis, which could fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Sound and Music Computing (cs.SD) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the issue of spurious correlations, which could be related to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Computation and Language (cs.CL) categories.
